{
  "texts": [
    "Following hexaploidization, genetic material from the other Ae.",
    "tauschii lineages (L1 and L3) became incorporated into the bread wheat D genome and were subsequently broken into smaller fragments via recombination.",
    "Although the proportions of alternative haplotype blocks are low in individual elite wheat cultivars, the different segments accumulate to considerable lengths across various genotypes.",
    "This notion is evidenced by the cumulative size of L3 segments that span a total of 666.0 Mb.",
    "We assessed 126 hexaploid wheat landraces, and although we selected for accessions with increased L3 genome content, it is likely that the proportion of remnant L3 segments in the bread wheat gene pool is even higher."
  ]
}